        <p>If you want your <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Flare">Word or FrameMaker </MadCap:conditionalText>output to have footers (to hold content such as text and page numbers), you can accomplish this by inserting a Page Footer proxy into a master page. The Page Footer proxy lets you insert content or automatic <MadCap:keyword term="Page numbers:printed output;Print-based output:page numbers" />page numbering (specifically designated for the first page, even pages, or odd pages) in a master page. Use the Page Footer proxy to insert content and page numbering below the Body proxy.</p>
